    "See Section A for further details about nilsolitons.",
    "Finally, in analogy with the homogeneous case (see [Lau11,§2] and the proof of Proposition A.2), the vector field X can be obtained from the nilsoliton derivation field D: Lemma 3.2.",
    "Let D ∈ Γ Der(adM) be a the derivation field corresponding to an invariant endomorphism D V ∈ End(V) inv, and let g be an invariant metric on M defining a flat connection H whose monodromy has no translational part.",
    "Then, there exists a vertical vector field X D ∈ Γ(T M) so thatL X D g = g(D M •, •) + g(•, D M •), where D M ∈ End(T M) inv is given according to T M = V ⊕ H by D M:= D V 0 0 0.Proof.",
    "The idea is to use local trivialisations, and argue as in [Lau11, §2] fibrewise."
